==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌst|-ʌst]]

===Adjective===
'''nonplussed'''

#Bewildered; unsure how to respond
#A [[neologism]] meaning unimpressed.

===Etymology===
Nonplussed is derived from the Latin phrase "non plus" meaning "no more, no further".
<ref name="The Mavens' Word of the Day">
{{cite web
| url = http://www.randomhouse.com/wotd/index.pperl?date=19991221
